Manager, Riv1, and Riv2 are sometimes referred to collectively herein as the “Parties,” and each separately as a “Party.” RECITALS: A. Riv1 is developing a solar photovoltaic electricity generating facility with a rated capacity of 20 MWac located in the Town of Calverton in Suffolk County, New York (the “Riv1 Project”) on the real property described in Exhibit A-1. The Riv1 Project includes photovoltaic modules, inverters, and related infrastructure. B. Riv2 is a solar photovoltaic electricity generating facility with a rated capacity of 36 MWac located adjacent to the Riv1 Project (the “Riv2 Project”) on the real property described in Exhibit A-2. The Riv2 Project includes photovoltaic modules, inverters, and related infrastructure. The Riv1 Project and Riv2 Project shall be referred to individually as a “Project” and together as the “Projects.” C. In connection with the Riv1 Project, Riv1 will design, construct, and own, on the land described in Exhibit B-1 (such land, the “Shared Premises”) a substation together with a generator interconnection line and other associated facilities connecting the Riv1 Project to the transmission system owned by Long Island Lighting Company d/b/a LIPA (“LIPA”) and controlled by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. (“NYISO”). The Parties are also holders of, or are acquiring, certain fee, lease, easement, license and permit rights, all of which are more particularly described on Exhibit B-2 (as amended and supplemented from time to time, the “Shared Premises Agreements”). D. Riv1 will construct, and Riv1 and Riv2 will share in the ongoing cost of, the Shared Facilities in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement. E. Each of Riv1 and Riv2 is pursuing its own agreement for interconnection services with the NYISO and LIPA. F. Riv1 and Riv2 also wish to contract with Manager for the provision of certain limited services to be performed at the pleasure of the Owners with respect to the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises, and the Manager wishes to accept said engagement, on the terms and conditions contained herein. AGREEMENT: NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants contained in this Agreement and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is acknowledged, the Parties agree as follows: 1. TERM; GRANT OF OPTION; EXERCISE OF OPTION; PURCHASE PRICE; CONDITIONS PRECEDENT TO CLOSING; CLOSING OF PURCHASE AND SALE 2.1 Term. This Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and remain in full force and effect following the Effective Date until the first occurrence of one of the following: (a) the mutual agreement of all the Parties, or (b) otherwise as may be provided under this Agreement. 2.2 Grant of Option. Upon the terms and subject to the conditions contained in this Agreement, Riv1 hereby grants to Riv2 an exclusive and irrevocable option, exercisable in Riv2’s sole and exclusive discretion, to purchase an Undivided Interest in a percentage amount equal to Riv2’s Percentage Interest and no less than Riv2’s Percentage Interest (such option being hereinafter referred to as the “Option”). For avoidance of doubt, after exercise of the Option described in this Section 2.2, Riv1 would retain for itself an Undivided Interest in a percentage amount equal to Riv1’s Percentage Interest. 2.3 Option Premium. For and in consideration for the grant of the Option to Riv2 by Riv1 and the continuing maintenance by Riv1 of such Option in full force and effect in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement, Riv2 hereby agrees to pay the Option Premium to Riv1 on the Effective Date. 2.4 Exercise of Option. Subject to the conditions contained in this Agreement, Riv2 may exercise the Option in whole only and not in part. Riv2 shall be entitled to exercise the Option at any time prior to the Option Deadline by delivery to Riv1 of written notice of its election to exercise the Option (the “Election Notice”). If the Option is not exercised prior to the Option Deadline, then it shall be extinguished and of no further force or effect effective upon and after the Option Deadline. 2.5 Purchase and Sale. In the event Riv2 exercises the Option, Riv1 shall sell, convey, assign, transfer and deliver to Riv2 an Undivided Interest in the Shared Facilities in the amount of the Percentage Interest subject to the Option under Section 2.2, on the terms and subject to the conditions contained in this Agreement. As of the time of the Closing, the Shared Facilities shall also include the following assets, but not the Excluded Assets: 2.5.1 Tangible Personal Property. All tangible personal property included in the Shared Facilities. 2.5.2 Supplies. The inventories of spare parts, lubricants and other fluids intended to be consumed at the Shared Facilities in the ordinary course of business, maintenance, shop and office materials and supplies, and other similar tangible personal property on hand at or in transit to the Shared Facilities as of the Closing and intended to be consumed at the Shared Facilities in the ordinary course of business. 2.5.3 Shared Facilities Contracts. All material contracts, agreements and personal property leases that are used in, relate primarily to or are necessary for the ownership or operation of the Shared Facilities, except for the Riv1 Interconnection Agreement, the Riv2 Interconnection Agreement and other agreements of a Party which will be separately entered into with NYISO or LIPA, and the Shared Premises Agreements. 2.5.4 Shared Facilities Permits. All material permits that are used in, related primarily to or are necessary for the ownership or operation of the Shared Facilities; provided, however, that, notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, Riv1, at its own expense, shall be obligated to comply with all compliance and mitigation obligations of any material permits related primarily to or necessary for the ownership or operation of Riv1’s Project or its Project Specific Assets. 2.5.5 Intangible Personal Property. All material intellectual property and all other intangible proprietary information or materials owned by or licensed to Riv1 and necessary for the ownership or operation of the Shared Facilities. 2.5.6 Warranties. All warranties that are unexpired as of the Closing that relate specifically to the Shared Facilities (the “Warranty Rights”). 2.5.7 Books and Records. All books and records used in, relating primarily to or necessary for the ownership or operation of the Shared Facilities (the “Books and Records”). 2.5.8 Incidental Assets. All of the following, insofar as the same are used in, related primarily to or are necessary for the ownership or operation of the Shared Facilities: (i) all purchase orders and certificates of title and documents; and (ii) all keys, lock combinations, computer access codes and other devices or information necessary to gain entry to or take possession of the Shared Facilities. 2.6 Excluded Assets. With respect to any Undivided Interest purchased by Riv2, the Shared Facilities shall not include any of the following assets of Riv1 (the “Excluded Assets”): 2.6.1 Claims; Other Rights of Recovery. All claims, causes of action, rights of recovery, rights of set-off, rights to refunds and similar rights of any kind in favor of Riv1 or any other Person arising from or relating to the operation of the Shared Facilities with respect to any period of time prior to the Closing, including any refund of taxes described in Section 2.6.2, except for (i) any of the foregoing that relate to Assumed Liabilities and (ii) the Warranty Rights. 2.6.2 Tax Refunds. All refunds or credits, if any, of taxes due to or from Riv1 or any other Person, excluding any refunds or credits to the extent attributable to taxes on or with respect to Riv2’s Undivided Interest that were imposed for a period (or portion thereof) beginning after the Closing. 2.6.3 Insurance. The rights under any insurance policy arising out of and relating to events or periods prior to the Closing or which is not related to the Shared Facilities, except to the extent such policy insures for events or occurrences that are included in the Assumed Liabilities. 2.6.4 Corporate Records. All books and records of Riv1 or any other Person other than the Books and Records. 2.7 Assumed Liabilities. At the Closing, Riv2 shall assume and agree to pay, perform and discharge when due, in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement, Riv2’s Percentage Interest share of all Liabilities related to the Shared Facilities or the ownership, possession, occupancy, or use thereof, in each case arising, to be performed, or attributable to the period from and after the Closing (the “Assumed Liabilities”). For the avoidance of doubt, the Assumed Liabilities shall include the following: 2.7.1 Obligations in Respect of Shared Facilities. All Liabilities in respect of the ownership, possession, occupancy, development, construction, improvement, maintenance, repair, use or operation of the Shared Facilities and under the Shared Premises Agreements. 2.7.2 Liabilities Under Shared Facilities Contracts and Shared Facilities Permits. All Liabilities under the Shared Facilities contracts (excluding those contracts expressly excluded pursuant to Section 2.5.3) and Shared Facilities permits arising or to be performed on or after the Closing (excluding those obligations excluded pursuant to Section 4). 2.7.3 Taxes. All Taxes related to the Shared Facilities or the Shared Premises or the ownership, possession, occupancy or use thereof. 2.8 Purchase Price. The purchase price (the “Purchase Price”) of an Undivided Interest in the Shared Facilities shall be One Dollar ($1.00). The Purchase Price shall be payable to Riv1 in cash in U.S. dollars. 2.9 Conditions to Obligations of Riv1. The obligations of Riv1 hereunder to sell an Undivided Interest to Riv2 are subject to the fulfillment, at or before the Closing of such sale, of each of the following conditions (all or any of which may be waived in whole or in part by Riv1 in its sole discretion): 2.9.1 Performance. Riv2 shall have performed and complied with, in all material respects, the agreements, covenants and obligations required by this Agreement to be so performed or complied with by Riv2 at or before the Closing. 2.9.2 Orders and Laws. There shall not be in effect on the Closing Date any Law restraining, enjoining, or otherwise prohibiting or making illegal the consummation of the sale of the Undivided Interest to Riv2 or any of the other transactions contemplated by this Agreement. 2.9.3 Consents and Approvals. All consents, approvals and actions of, filings with and notices to any Governmental Authority necessary to permit Riv1 and Riv2 to perform their obligations under this Agreement, and to consummate the transactions contemplated hereby and thereby, including FERC approval under Section 203 of the Federal Power Act, if required, shall have been duly obtained, made or given and shall be in full force and effect, and all terminations or expirations of waiting periods imposed by any Governmental Authority necessary for the consummation of the transactions contemplated by this Agreement shall have occurred. 2.9.4 Interconnection Agreements. Riv2 shall have entered into a fully executed interconnection agreement or agreements as contemplated in Section 6.4 (any such agreement, the “Riv2 Interconnection Agreement”). 2.9.5 Deliveries. Riv2 shall have executed and delivered to Riv1 all other agreements, instruments and documents required to be delivered by Riv2 under Section 2.12.2. 2.10 Conditions to Obligations Riv2. The obligations of Riv2 hereunder to purchase an Undivided Interest from Riv1 are subject to the fulfillment, at or before the Closing, of each of the following conditions (all or any of which may be waived in whole or in part by Riv2 in its sole discretion): 2.10.1 Performance. Riv1 shall have performed and complied with, in all material respects, the agreements, covenants and obligations required by this Agreement to be so performed or complied with by Riv1 at or before the Closing. 2.10.2 Orders and Laws. SHARED ASSETS 3.1 Shared Facilities. Riv1 plans to design and construct the Shared Facilities that are governed by this Agreement. The Parties acknowledge and agree that unless and until there is any other Owner under this Agreement, Riv1 shall be the sole Party with title to the Shared Facilities and its Percentage Interest shall be one hundred percent (100%). 3.2 Partial Conveyance of Co-Tenancy Interests in Shared Facilities. 3.2.1 Effective on the Closing, upon and subject to the terms, conditions, restrictions and reservations set forth in this Agreement, Riv1 shall be deemed to have transferred to Riv2 an undivided ownership interest in and to the Shared Facilities owned or hereafter acquired by Riv1, equal to Riv2’s Percentage Interest, AS IS, WITH ALL FAULTS AND WITHOUT (EXCEPT AS AND TO THE EXTENT OTHERWISE EXPRESSLY PROVIDED IN THIS AGREEMENT) ANY REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES WHATSOEVER, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, AND SPECIFICALLY EXCLUDING ANY WARRANTY OF TITLE, MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR ANY OTHER WARRANTY ARISING UNDER STATUTORY OR COMMON LAW, while at the same time reserving to itself an undivided ownership interest in and to such Shared Facilities in the amount of the Riv1 Percentage Interest. The intent of the foregoing is that each Owner shall each own an undivided interest as a tenant in common in the Shared Facilities equal to such Owner’s respective Percentage Interest so as to provide for the joint ownership of the Shared Facilities (along with all appurtenant rights) by the Owners subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. The foregoing undivided interest of each Owner in the Shared Facilities may be referred to from time to time in this Agreement as an “Undivided Interest.” 3.2.2 Without limiting the provisions of Section 2.12.1, on the Closing Date, or within a reasonable time thereafter, Riv1 shall deliver to Riv2 any other notices, instruments, documents, agreements or consents as are reasonably necessary in connection with the ownership of Riv2’s respective Undivided Interest. 3.3 Shared Premises Agreements and Land Matters. 3.3.1 An Owner’s exercise of rights with respect to an Undivided Interest in applicable Shared Facilities shall be subject to such Owner having rights under the applicable Shared Premises Agreements to use the Shared Premises on which the applicable Shared Facilities are located. Each Owner shall comply with all the terms and conditions of the Shared Premises Agreements, the Land Matters, and the Governmental Approvals. 3.3.2 Subject to their authority or ability to do so, the Parties and Owners shall timely execute the necessary instruments to ensure each Owner has sufficient rights to use the applicable Shared Premises on which the Shared Facilities are located. Manager will add such instruments to the Shared Premises Agreements. 3.3.3 Any amounts due under the terms of the Shared Premises Agreements shall be paid by the Manager, subject to reimbursement by the Owners in accordance with Section 4. 3.3.4 No Shared Premises Agreement may be terminated, modified or amended without the consent of all of the Owners that are party to, or that directly enjoy rights or benefits under, such Shared Premises Agreement. Nevertheless, if an Owner wishes to terminate its interest in a Shared Premises Agreement, and such termination (i) is permitted by the Shared Premises Agreement itself or by the counterparty thereto and (ii) will have no adverse effect on the other Owner thereto, then Owner may terminate its interest in that Shared Premises Agreement. The permitted termination by an Owner of its interest in a Shared Premises Agreement shall not cause or be deemed to cause the release of such Owner for any Liabilities or obligations accruing prior to such termination. 3.4 Access to Shared Facilities. Subject to Section 3.3, each Owner and its Representatives shall have access to the Shared Facilities (a) for inspection of the Shared Facilities, (b) for any required maintenance of the Shared Facilities agreed to be undertaken by the Owners or not performed by the Manager in accordance with Section 8, (c) for the installation, maintenance, or repairs of the Shared Facilities or Project Specific Assets, and (d) for the operation of the Shared Facilities, all in accordance with this Agreement. Notwithstanding the foregoing, except in the event of an Emergency, each Owner shall provide no less than twenty-four (24) hours’ prior notice to Manager and the other Owner of its intent to access the Shared Facilities, and no less than forty-eight (48) hours’ prior notice to Manager and the other Owner prior to performing any maintenance or repairs pursuant to clause (b) or (c) above. The Manager, an Owner and/or any Owner’s Representatives shall follow all applicable safety, security and site rules established by the agreement of the Owners and Manager, and shall comply with all applicable Shared Premises Agreements, Land Matters, Laws and Governmental Approvals when on the Shared Premises or accessing the Shared Facilities, except to the extent that following any such rule would violate applicable Law. In the event of an Emergency, prior notice is not required to access the Shared Facilities to respond to the Emergency, but the Owner shall provide notice of access to Manager and the other Owner as soon as reasonably practicable thereafter (no more than twenty-four (24) hours after access). 3.5 No Interference, Cooperation and Over-Burdening. An Owner’s use of the Shared Assets or the operation of its Project may not interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Owner of its rights in such Shared Assets or the operation of its Project, except as specifically provided herein. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, including Section 6.13, each of the Owners shall cooperate in good faith to accommodate each of the other Owner’s use of the Shared Assets for the benefit the other’s Projects as contemplated by this Agreement. Each Owner acknowledges and agrees that the use of the Shared Assets by the Projects as contemplated herein does not, separately or in the aggregate, constitute an overburdening of the Shared Assets, or any part thereof. No Owner will use or permit the use of the Shared Assets in any manner that would create waste or nuisance, or that would jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to the Shared Assets or any Governmental Approval as to the Shared Assets or any Project, nor otherwise conduct or cause to be conducted operations on its Project Site or on the Shared Premises that would have similar effects on, or otherwise damage or interfere with, the Shared Assets. 3.6 Additional Real Property Rights and Facilities. 3.6.1 To the extent that any additional real property and rights therein (“Additional Shared Premises”) or physical facilities (“Additional Shared Facilities,” and together with the Additional Shared Premises, the “Additional Shared Assets”) that relate to the Shared Assets or operation thereof, are required by any Owner (to reach Commercial Operation of a Project, continue operating a Project or repower a Project), the Owner or the Manager may give written notice to the other Owner of such requirement, with a reasonable explanation of why such Additional Shared Assets are needed. The Owner receiving such notice shall have thirty (30) days after receiving such notice to determine if such Additional Shared Assets are also needed for its Project and to so notify the other Owner and Manager in writing of its election to participate in the acquisition, installation, and/or construction of such Additional Shared Assets. An Owner’s failure to notify the other Owner and Manager of its election to participate within such thirty (30) day period will be deemed an election to decline the addition of the proposed Additional Shared Assets to the Shared Assets. Any Additional Shared Assets that the Owners agree to add to the Shared Assets to be governed by this Agreement shall be (a) procured jointly by the Owners, (b) added to the Shared Premises and/or Shared Facilities, as applicable, under this Agreement, and (c) held in undivided ownership interests by the Owners. If the other Owner does not agree to add Additional Shared Assets requested by an Owner or the Manager under this Section 3.6.1, then nothing herein shall prevent the requesting Owner from acquiring the additional premises or facilities needed by and to be held by such Owner, not as part of the Shared Assets hereunder, and not subject to the terms of this Agreement, provided that any additional facilities so acquired shall not, in the reasonable judgment of both Manager and the other Owner, interfere with the development, construction, operation, usage or the maintenance of the Shared Assets or the other Project, or otherwise violate the terms and conditions of this Agreement, the Land Matters, Governmental Approvals or applicable Laws. Nothing contained herein shall require that an Owner be required to reimburse the other Owner for any Additional Shared Assets unless it has expressly agreed to do so in writing. 3.6.2 Except as otherwise provided in this Agreement, no Owner shall construct, install or place any additional facilities within the Shared Premises. 3.7 Conditions to Installation of Additional Shared Facilities or Connecting Projects to the Shared Facilities. Any Owner installing Additional Shared Facilities or connecting its Project to the Shared Facilities shall (a) not interfere with the use or access by the other Owner of the Shared Facilities, except as may be necessary during the installation, repair, or replacement of Shared Facilities, (b) to the extent commercially reasonable, schedule during an off-peak and/or low solar insolation period any required disconnection of the Shared Facilities to conduct construction activities to minimize the impact on the Project of the other Owner, (c) provide at least thirty (30) days’ prior written notice of commencement of such construction activities together with a reasonably detailed description thereof, (d) provide at least thirty (30) days’ prior written notice of any planned outages, and the durations thereof, of the Shared Facilities that would result in a disconnection of the other Owner’s Project, (e) take into consideration, to the extent commercially reasonable, any changes in the construction plans or timing of construction required by the other Owner, provided that the other Owner does not attempt to interfere with the installation of the proposed Additional Shared Facilities, unless such installation can reasonably be expected to result in an Emergency or violate the terms of the Shared Premises Agreements, the Land Matters, Governmental Approvals, or this Agreement, (f) be responsible for obtaining and complying with any necessary Governmental Approvals and providing documentary evidence of such Governmental Approvals to the Owners and Manager, and (g) compensate the other Owner’s Project for all lost revenues as a result of lost generation due to an outage or disconnection of such Owner’s Project. Any Owner (i) installing Additional Shared Facilities that are not needed by or would not benefit the other Owner, or (ii) connecting its own Project to the Shared Facilities, shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Owner from all Liabilities, including third party claims, property and revenue losses incurred, as a result of such construction or installation activities, but such installing Owner may seek reimbursement for such indemnified costs from insurance required by Section 12 to the extent such insurance provides coverage for such indemnified costs. Installation of Additional Shared Facilities that are needed by or would benefit all Owners and that are expressly consented to by such Owners, shall be installed jointly by the Owners or by the Manager at the direction of the Owners and will be at the risk of all the Owners, and each Owner shall have the right to review and approve all design, planning and installation elements in connection with such installation, and will bear any risk of loss thereof in proportion with its Percentage Interest in the Additional Shared Facilities, to the extent such loss is not covered by the insurance required by Section 12. 4. SHARED EXPENSES 4.1 Liabilities for the Account of the Owners; No Charging of Fees, Premiums or Profits. Except as specifically set forth in this Agreement, each Party shall be solely responsible for its Liabilities relating to its Project and Project Specific Assets, including without limitation, all Liabilities arising from acquiring, designing, installing, constructing, using, operating, maintaining and repairing its Project Specific Assets. Each Party shall, at its sole cost and expense, maintain in good working order and repair at all times each part of its Project that connects with, will connect with, or affects the Shared Facilities or the Shared Premises. Each Owner (or Owners, if any Additional Shared Assets are being acquired or installed at the joint expense of both Owners) acquiring or installing any Additional Shared Assets shall be responsible for, and pay, all Liabilities relating to the acquisition or installation, as applicable, of the Additional Shared Assets, except to the extent otherwise provided in Section 3.7.
